<u>Installation of packages:</u><ol>
<li> Select <i>"$I18N_package_selection"</i>, <i>"$I18N_normal_packages"</i> or <i>"$I18N_special_packages"</i>.</li>
<li> Enter your search key at <i>"$I18N_package_search"</i>. If you leave the field blank all packages matching the package criteria are displayed. Please note that this doesn't work if you select <i>"$I18N_normal_packages"</i> because of the huge amount of normal packages.</li>
<li> At <i>"$I18N_found_packages"</i> you can see all packages matching your search criteria.</li>
<li> Check the checkbox beside all the packages you want to install.</li>
<li> Preselect your chosen packages by clicking on <i>"$I18N_preselect"</i>.</li>
<li> Repeat step 1-5 if required.</li></ol>

Complete the installation by clicking on <i>"Install preselected packages"</i>.

Now you have preselected packages for installation. <!-- v1.5-->A green check mark shows that the package will be installed on the client and a red cross that the package will be removed. <!--end v1.5-->You can remove packages from the installation list by checking the packages <!-- v12.3-->(by clicking on the symbols at the top of the checkbox column you can select all or no packages or invert your selection)<!-- end v12.3--> and clicking on <i>"$I18N_discard_selected"</i> or all packages by clicking on <i>"$I18N_discard_all"</i>.

Install the packages with a click on <i>"$I18N_install_selected"</i>.

